@startuml Sequence_Tailor_Workflow

actor Tailor
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend API" as API
database "Database" as DB
actor Customer
actor Admin

== Tailor Accepts and Works on Order ==

Tailor -> Frontend: View Assigned Order
Frontend -> API: GET /api/orders/:id
API -> DB: Fetch order
DB --> API: Order details
API --> Frontend: Order data
Frontend --> Tailor: Order details\n(measurements, fabric, notes)

Tailor -> Frontend: Accept Order
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/orders/:id/accept
API -> DB: Update order\n(acceptedByTailor = true,\nstatus = "Cutting")
DB --> API: Order updated

API -> DB: Create notification for admin
DB --> API: Notification created

API --> Frontend: Order accepted
Frontend --> Tailor: Confirmation

== Tailor Starts Work ==

Tailor -> Frontend: Start Work on Order
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/orders/:id/start-work
API -> DB: Update order\n(workStartedAt = now,\nstatus = "Cutting")
DB --> API: Order updated

API -> DB: Create notifications\n(for Admin & Customer)
DB --> API: Notifications created

API --> Frontend: Work started
Frontend --> Tailor: Confirmation

DB -> Admin: Notification: "Tailor started work"
DB -> Customer: Notification: "Order being worked on"

== Tailor Updates Order Stage ==

Tailor -> Frontend: Update to Next Stage
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/orders/:id/next-stage
API -> DB: Fetch current order
DB --> API: Order (status = "Cutting")

API -> DB: Update order\n(status = "Stitching")
DB --> API: Order updated

API --> Frontend: Stage updated
Frontend --> Tailor: Status: "Stitching"

== Tailor Marks Order Ready ==

Tailor -> Frontend: Mark Order as Ready
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/orders/:id/mark-ready
API -> DB: Update order\n(status = "Ready",\ncompletedAt = now)
DB --> API: Order updated

API -> DB: Create notifications\n(for Admin & Customer)
DB --> API: Notifications created

API --> Frontend: Order marked ready
Frontend --> Tailor: Confirmation

DB -> Admin: Notification: "Order ready for delivery"
DB -> Customer: Notification: "Order ready for collection"

== Customer Views Ready Order ==

Customer -> Frontend: View Orders
Frontend -> API: GET /api/orders
API -> DB: Fetch customer orders
DB --> API: Orders (status = "Ready")
API --> Frontend: Orders list
Frontend --> Customer: Display ready orders

note right of DB
  Order Status Flow:
  Pending → Cutting → Stitching → Ready
end note

@enduml


